==English==

===Etymology===

Latin ''tuberculum'' (diminutive of ''tuber'', lump) + -''osis'' (diseased condition).

===Noun===
'''tuberculosis''' (''plural'' '''tuberculoses''')

# {{pathology}} An infectious disease of humans and animals caused by a species of [[Mycobacterium]] mainly infecting the [[lung]]s where it causes [[tubercle]]s characterized by the [[expectoration]] of [[mucus]] and [[sputum]], [[fever]], weight loss, and chest pain. Transmission is through inhalation or ingestion of [[bacteria]].

